## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="64f8d-102">Une instance de <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.EmulateRecognizeCompletedEventArgs> est créé lorsque le <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine> objet déclenche le <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine.EmulateRecognizeCompleted> événement.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="64f8d-102">An instance of <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.EmulateRecognizeCompletedEventArgs> is created when the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine> object raises the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine.EmulateRecognizeCompleted> event.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="64f8d-103">Pour obtenir des informations sur le résultat de la reconnaissance, accédez à la <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.EmulateRecognizeCompletedEventArgs.Result%2A> propriété dans le gestionnaire pour l’événement.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="64f8d-103">To obtain information about the result of recognition, access the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.EmulateRecognizeCompletedEventArgs.Result%2A> property in the handler for the event.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="64f8d-104">Émulation est le processus par lequel le texte, au lieu de l’audio, est l’entrée à un module de reconnaissance vocale.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="64f8d-104">Emulation is the process by which text, instead of audio, is the input to a speech recognition engine.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="64f8d-105">Pour ignorer les entrées audio pour un <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine> l’objet au cours de l’émulation, utilisez le <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine.SetInputToNull%2A> (méthode).</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="64f8d-105">To bypass the audio inputs for a <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine> object during emulation, use the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine.SetInputToNull%2A> method.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="64f8d-106">Si le moteur de reconnaissance vocale rencontre une exception pendant l’opération de reconnaissance, les <xref:System.ComponentModel.AsyncCompletedEventArgs.Error%2A> propriété est définie à l’exception et la <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.EmulateRecognizeCompletedEventArgs.Result%2A> propriété est définie sur `null`.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="64f8d-106">If the speech recognition engine encounters an exception during the recognition operation, the <xref:System.ComponentModel.AsyncCompletedEventArgs.Error%2A> property is set to the exception and the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.EmulateRecognizeCompletedEventArgs.Result%2A> property is set to `null`.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="64f8d-107"><xref:System.Speech.Recognition.EmulateRecognizeCompletedEventArgs> dérive de <xref:System.ComponentModel.AsyncCompletedEventArgs>.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="64f8d-107"><xref:System.Speech.Recognition.EmulateRecognizeCompletedEventArgs> derives from <xref:System.ComponentModel.AsyncCompletedEventArgs>.</span></span>  
  
   
  
## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="64f8d-108">L’exemple suivant ajoute un gestionnaire d’événements pour le <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine.EmulateRecognizeCompleted> événement à un <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine>.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="64f8d-108">The following example adds an event handler for the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine.EmulateRecognizeCompleted> event to a <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine>.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="64f8d-109">Le gestionnaire obtient le texte reconnu à partir de la <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.EmulateRecognizeCompletedEventArgs.Result%2A> propriété.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="64f8d-109">The handler gets the recognized text from the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.EmulateRecognizeCompletedEventArgs.Result%2A> property.</span></span>  
  
```csharp  
  
private SpeechRecognitionEngine sre;  
  
// Initialize the speech recognition engine.   
private void Initialize()  
{  
  sre = new SpeechRecognitionEngine();  
  
  // Add a handler for the EmulateRecognizeCompleted event.  
  sre.EmulateRecognizeCompleted += new EventHandler<EmulateRecognizeCompletedEventArgs>(sre_EmulateRecognizeCompleted);  
  
  // Add other initialization code here.  
}  
  
// Handle the EmulateRecognizeCompleted event.   
void sre_EmulateRecognizeCompleted(object sender, EmulateRecognizeCompletedEventArgs e)  
{  
  if (e.Result == null) return;  
  
  string phrase = e.Result.Text;  
  
  // Add event handler code here.  
}  
  
```
